# Project Structure & Conventions

## Folder Layout

```
Notes/
├── index.html              ← Global index (links to all course folders)
├── styles.css              ← SINGLE global stylesheet — never duplicate it
└── Course Folder Name/
    ├── index.html          ← Course index (links to all topic pages)
    └── topic-name.html     ← Individual concept/notes page
```

- Each **course** lives in its own folder. Folder names are human-readable (e.g. `All Reinforcement Learning (RL) concepts`).
- Each **topic page** sits directly inside the course folder — no sub-folders.
- `styles.css` is at the root. **Never copy it into subfolders.**

## File Naming

| Page type | Convention | Example |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| Topic page | kebab-case, descriptive | `q-learning.html`, `deepseek-r1.html` |
| Course index | always `index.html` | `All Reinforcement Learning (RL) concepts/index.html` |
| Global index | always `index.html` | `Notes/index.html` |

- Use **lowercase kebab-case** for all new topic files.
- Never use spaces or underscores in file names.

## CSS Path Rules

- Notes pages (inside a course folder): `<link rel="stylesheet" href="../styles.css" />`
- Global index: `<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css" />`

## Updating the Index — Required Every Time

When a new topic page is added:
1. Add a `<a href="topic.html" class="module-card">` entry to the **course index**.
2. If it's a new course, also add a card to the **global index** (`Notes/index.html`) and increment the course count stat.
3. Place the card under the correct `<div class="section-divider">` group. Create a new section divider if needed.
4. **Never leave a notes page unlinked from its course index.**

## WIP Cards

If a page is planned but not yet written, add the card with class `wip`:
```html
<div class="module-card wip">...</div>
```
Switch to `<a href="...">` and remove `wip` once the page exists.
